<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName authority="Mulsant, 1850" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Aspidimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidimerus nigrovittatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrovittatus">Aspidimerus nigrovittatus</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1866 is not keyed in the present paper, because the description given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Motschulsky, V" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Socie ́ te ́ impe ́ riale des naturalistes de Moscou" pageId="20" pageNumber="67" pagination="393 - 446" title="Essai d'un Catalogue des Insectes de I'ile de Ceylan. Supplement." volume="39" year="1866">Motschulsky (1866)</bibRefCitation>
is too simple to diagnose: &quot;Subovatus, convexus, nitidus, sparsim puberulus, pallide flavus, elytris utrinque vitta lata nigra, apice non attinguenda&quot;. Additionally, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kapur, AP" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="20" pageNumber="67" pagination="77 - 128" title="A revision of the tribe Aspidimerini Weise (Coleoptera, Coccinellidae)." url="10.1111/j.1365-2311.1948.tb01233.x" volume="99" year="1948">Kapur (1948)</bibRefCitation>
declared that its type was not available.
</paragraph>
